Singapore Stocks: Golden Agri, Noble, Olam, Sim Lian, Wing Tai

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   B u r g o s
-- 
2011-08-31T04:45:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-31/ccm-olam-sim-lian-group-wing-tai-singapore-equity-preview.html
Singapore ’s Straits Times Index
gained 1.7 percent to 2,838.41 as of 12:40 p.m. local time,
trimming this month’s losses to 11 percent. All but two stocks
in the index of 30 companies advanced.  The following shares were among the most active in the
market. Stock symbols are in parentheses after the company name.  Commodity suppliers: The Thomson Reuters/Jefferies CRB
Index, which tracks prices of 19 commodities from copper to corn,
increased 1.1 percent in  New York  yesterday, extending its
advance for a fourth day.  Noble Group Ltd. (NOBL) ,, a Hong Kong-based supplier of
energy, food and mining commodities, rose 3.6 percent to S$1.585.
 Olam International Ltd. (OLAM)  , a supplier of agricultural
commodities, jumped 6.9 percent to S$2.49. The company said
fourth-quarter net income increased 38 percent from a year
earlier to S$127.4 million ($105.7 million).  Palm-oil producers: Crude palm-oil futures for November
delivery rose as much as 1.7 percent in  Kuala Lumpur  today,
heading for its first increase in four days.  Golden Agri-Resources Ltd. (GGR)  , the world’s second-
biggest palm-oil producer by sales, climbed 3.2 percent to 65.5
Singapore cents.  Indofood Agri Resources Ltd. (IFAR)  , the
plantation unit of  Indonesia ’s No. 1 noodle maker, gained 3.3
percent to S$1.405.  Wilmar International Ltd. (WIL)  , the
world’s biggest palm-oil processor, increased 1.4 percent to
S$5.25.  Sim Lian Group Ltd. (SLG)  , a property developer and
construction company, advanced 7 percent to 53.5 Singapore cents.
The company said full-year net income doubled to S$200 million
from a year earlier.  Wing Tai Holdings Ltd. (WINGT)  , a developer of high-end
residential properties in Singapore, surged 7.6 percent to
S$1.35. The company said fourth-quarter net income more than
doubled to S$170.6.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan Burgos in Singapore at 
 jburgos4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Gentle at 
 ngentle2@bloomberg.net . 